1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on predicting the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on vision-enabled devices, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The methodology proposed in the paper involves the use of a neural network (PreVIousNet) to build accurate predictive models, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict the performance of CNNs on IoT devices. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the performance of CNNs on low-power low-cost devices, which is related to the hardware architecture of such devices. 
5. cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper focuses on predicting the performance of CNNs on embedded platforms, which falls under the domain of embedded systems.
